http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/108-ambulance-workers-to-go-on-strike-from-January-24/article13995019.ece

Free ambulance services under the Arogya Kavacha scheme across the State are likely to be affected as drivers of the 108 services will launch an indefinite strike from January 24.M. Krishnamurthy, Bahujan Samaj Party (BSP) leader, announced the protest at a calendar release function, organised by the Arogya Kavacha scheme workers at the Department of Health and Family Welfare here on Monday.The workers have been demanding minimum wages and reduction of working hours for the past several years. However, the authorities did not heed to their demands, he said.Hence, the workers have decided to launch the protest, Mr. Krishnamurthy said.Mandya district ‘108 Ambulance Drivers’ union president Sunil, vice-president Shivanna, State unit president Lokesh, Mysuru unit president Mallikarjun, and Ramanagaram unit president Shivakumar were present.Mandya district has 21 ambulances and the workers attend 3,000 to 4,000 calls in a month, H.P. Manchegowda, District Health Officer, said.Speaking to The Hindu here, the DHO said that the department will make alternative arrangements, including arranging temporary drivers to operate the vehicles.